extract: Don't not ever take anything out with Telkom. They are liars and scammers!! I have logged a complaint to my legal team, My broadband as well ISPA against Telkom who has lied and misled me, as this has been going on for months now, I have taken out a Samsung Galaxy S21 Ultra for R699 at Telkom In January 2022, The phone was supposed to come with a Samsung original S case and S pen, as well as 20GB every month for the first 3 months. Upon arrival of my device, I have not received any of the promotional things mentioned above as they advertised on their website other than the 20GB data only for one month. I called in week after week and month after month, yet still nothing. It has been 5 months now since I received my phone and nothing has been done. They created tickets, but it has been closed with nothing being resolved, I called in multiple times and no one has done anything. I went to three Telkom stores and was told that they cannot help me as I got the phone from Telkom online and not in-store. Telkom told me to go onto the Samsung membership app to claim the promotional items yet they did not provide me with any code to claim or redeem. I have then reached out to Telkom again and they have not given me anything. After this, I went to Samsung who informed me that Telkom does this on a regular basis and leaves it to Samsung to sort it as if they created a mess. A month ago I was called after lodging this complaint since January by a gentleman working for Telkom where I have requested again to be put through to management but they have refused just as they do every time I ask them to have this escalated to management. Since the call, no one from Telkom has reached out to me and I am still waiting for them to contact me, yet my payments still go off every month as normal

extract: I have 3 LTE routers.Not strange. I had two children that was students and 1 for myself.I upgrade last year Nov to the special 80 + 80 for R199 each on all 3 LTE services.That was what was advertised. All the time,the amount goes off with 3 debit orders from my bank account.All of a sudden this month,my account was sky high and subtracted a hugh amount from my bank account.After a hunt for a Gestapo call centre,I was informed that my spending limit was reached and that data was loaded automatically by 1,5 times the rate.Who gave them the permission?The one router has 134G in credit as it rolled over from the previous month.Almost a year ago one of the routers data was capped and I have to buy extra data to goes on.Who ask them,or change something to a spent limit which was not set.They told me that 202G was used in one day which is bull.I worked for Telkom for 40 years and was retrenched in 2020.I never ever think that I will reach a day where I say this because I was loyal to the company.But they made me furious. And as soon as I come to a front office,I will ccld all 3 my LTE routers and my cellphone's contracts.

extract: A whole month and you guys can't bother to respond to my support request? I have been with you since 2019 and this is how treat me? You always respond, but now because you messed up my invoice there has been no response for over 30 days? Sis! I'm seriously thinking of leaving you. I've never been so disappointed in a service provider and I've been with Telkom before. I want my invoice fixed! I don't owe you guys for March. On 25 February you switched off my service due to non payment. At that point I owed you for both January and February, but and I'm really damn sorry I had no money to pay you. I'm a college student and was waiting for funds which came and I payed you in April. So for the whole month of March when I couldn't pay you, you decided to charge me is this some sick joke? Do you just like taking money from people who doesn't even have any to begin with? I want an advisor to contact me and sort this out. I want to do a Sim swop too. Your website is not allowing me to do so. South Africa still no action on this I was promised a call back from your billing department. A consultant called me told me I was charged for my subscription. Since when do you guys charge for subscriptions? Rain has always been a pay as you go service. You restricted me and I couldn't use my service but yet you still charge me for the month. It's been over a week since I got a call from you and you just made empty promises! I want my damn refund you have no right charging me for month that I didn't use. If I don't get a response within the 24 hours you are going to see what I do. I want my money back!
